One Christian song that may describe the sentiment or situation in this passage is "Great Is Thy Faithfulness" by Thomas Chisholm. This hymn emphasizes God's faithfulness and His provision even during difficult times. The lyrics include lines such as:

"Great is Thy faithfulness, O God my Father, 
There is no shadow of turning with Thee;
Thou changest not, Thy compassions, they fail not;
As Thou hast been, Thou forever will be."

In the context of the passage, we can see God's faithfulness to Noah and his family as He carries them through the flood and eventually allows them to exit the ark safely. The song explores the steadfast nature of God's love and His unwavering commitment to His people.
